                            <comment id="448579" author="adilger" created="Tue, 18 Mar 2025 07:49:31 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This was removed in patch &lt;a href=&quot;http://review.whamcloud.com/19368&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://review.whamcloud.com/19368&lt;/a&gt; (&quot;&lt;tt&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-7990&quot; title=&quot; Large bulk IO support&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-7990&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-7990&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; clio: revise readahead to support 16MB IO&lt;/tt&gt;&quot;).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="54192" author="adilger" created="Sat, 16 Mar 2013 04:25:31 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;d prefer not to have a new /proc tunable if we don&apos;t need it - we have enough already.  It probably makes more sense to increase this with the actual RPC size and/or the stripe size.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
